UNITED STATES v. UNION PAC. R. CO. (two cases). (Circuit Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. January 5, 1915.) Nos. 4242, 4243. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the District of Wyoming. Charles L. Higdon, TI. S. Atty., of Cheyenne, Wyo., for the United States. Herbert V. Lacey and John W. Lacey, both of Cheyenne, Wyo., for defendant in error.

Before HOOK and GARLAND, Circuit Judges, and AMIDON, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed, without costs to either party in this court, per stipulation of parties.
